This article describes the setup of USB (Universal Serial Bus) controllers.

== Installation ==

=== Hardware detection ===

To choose the right driver, first detect the used USB controllers. The {{c|[[Hardware detection|lspci]]}} utility works nicely for this task:

{{RootCmd|lspci {{!}} grep --color -i usb}}

=== Kernel ===

See the kernel section of the [[USB/Guide#Config_options_for_the_kernel|USB guide]] and the USB host controllers section of the [[Kernel/Gentoo_Kernel_Configuration_Guide#USB_host_controllers|Kernel configuration guide]].

=== Portage ===

Portage knows the [https://packages.gentoo.org/useflags/usb <code>usb</code> USE flag]. Some packages include or exclude support for USB based on this flag. As with all [[USE flag]]s, can be set as a value of the <var>USE</var> variable in {{Path|[[:/etc/portage/make.conf#USE|/etc/portage/make.conf]]}} or in {{Path|[[:/etc/portage/package.use]]}}.

=== Emerge ===

Install the {{Package|sys-apps/usbutils}} package, if it is not already installed by adding the [https://packages.gentoo.org/useflags/usb <code>usb</code> USE flag] and re-running emerge with <code>--changed-use</code>:

{{Emerge|sys-apps/usbutils}}

